title: PML-N Candidate Malik Asad Ali  wins PP-160 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz candidate Malik Asad Ali won the Punjab Assembly elections from PP-82,(Lahore -XVI) by securing 26,781 votes.
According to unofficial results, issued by the returning officer/ECP, the runner-up was Independent Candidate Azam Khan Niazi 21,249 votes.
Overall voters turnout remained 40.84 percent.
